test.name: Automate an Android Calculator App

kw.name: Open Application
kw.doc: Opens a new application to given Appium server. Capabilities of appium server, Android and iOS, Please check https://github.com/appium/appium/blob/master/docs/en/writing-running-appium/server-args.md | *Option* | *Man.* | *Description* | | remote_url | Yes | Appium server url | | alias | no | alias | | strict_ssl | No | allows you to send commands to an invalid certificate host like a self-signed one. |

kw.name: Clear Text
kw.doc: Clears the text field identified by `locator`.

kw.name: Wait Until Page Contains Element
kw.doc: Waits until element specified with `locator` appears on current page.

kw.name: Click Element
kw.doc: Click element identified by `locator`.

kw.name: Get Text
kw.doc: Get element text (for hybrid and mobile browser use `xpath` locator, others might cause problem)

kw.name: Log
kw.doc: Logs the given message with the given level.

kw.name: Get Activity
kw.doc: Retrieves the current activity on the device.

kw.name: Get Appium SessionId
kw.doc: Returns the current session ID as a reference

kw.name: Get Appium Timeout
kw.doc: Gets the timeout in seconds that is used by various keywords.

kw.name: Get Capability
kw.doc: Return the desired capability value by desired capability name

kw.name: Get Contexts
kw.doc: Get available contexts.

kw.name: Get Current Context
kw.doc: Get current context.

kw.name: Get Element Rect
kw.doc: Gets dimensions and coordinates of an element

kw.name: Get Element Size
kw.doc: Get element size

kw.name: Get Network Connection Status
kw.doc: Returns an integer bitmask specifying the network connection type.

kw.name: Get Source
kw.doc: Returns the entire source of the current page.
